First Read: 20-Jan-26
SB183 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the Alabama Board of Cosmetology and
5 Barbering; to amend Sections 34-7B-1 and 34-7B-13, Code of
6 Alabama 1975; to remove braiding and weaving hair from the
7 definition of "cosmetology"; to remove the licensure
8 requirement from the definition of "natural hairstylist"; to
9 provide that a license from the Alabama Board of Cosmetology
10 and Barbering is not required to perform natural hair styling;
11 to provide that persons who otherwise meet the requirements
12 for a natural hairstylist license may voluntarily acquire a
13 natural hairstylist license; to further provide that students
14 may acquire a voluntary natural hairstylist license through a
15 public high school cosmetology program; and to make
16 nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the existing
17 code language to current style.
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
19 Section 1. Sections 34-7B-1 and 34-7B-13, Code of
20 Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
21 "§34-7B-1
22 For the purposes of this chapter, the following terms
23 shall have the following meanings:
24 (1) APPRENTICE. Any person engaged in learning the
25 practices defined in this article including, but not limited
26 to, assisting in the performance of any acts of barbering or
27 cosmetology on the general public under the constant and
28 direct supervision of a person who has held a valid current
