29 license issued by the board for at least five years, in a shop
30 licensed by the board.
31 (2) BARBERING. The occupation of shaving or trimming
32 the beard, cutting or dressing the hair, giving facial or
33 scalp massages, giving facial or scalp treatment with oils or
34 creams or other preparations made for that purpose, either by
35 hand or by means of mechanical appliances, singeing and
36 shampooing the hair, dyeing the hair, or permanently waving or
37 straightening the hair of any living or deceased person for
38 compensation, as performed by a Class 2 barber.
39 (3) BOARD. The Alabama Board of Cosmetology and
40 Barbering.
41 (4) CLASS 1 BARBER. A person who only does the
42 following in his or her ordinary course of business: Arranges,
43 cleans, cuts, or singes the hair of any person or massages,
44 cleans, stimulates, exercises, or does similar work on the
45 scalp, face, or neck of any person with the hands, or with
46 mechanical or electrical apparatus or appliance, or by the use
47 of cosmetic preparations, antiseptics, tonics, lotions, or
48 creams. Any one or a combination of the following practices,
49 when done upon the human body above the seventh cervical
50 vertebra for cosmetic purposes and not for the treatment of
51 disease or physical or mental ailments, and when done for
52 payment, directly or indirectly, or without payment for the
53 public generally: Shaving or trimming the beard or trimming
54 the hair.
55 (5) CLASS 2 BARBER. Any person, other than a student or
56 apprentice, who performs barbering on the general public for
Page 2

