153 "§34-7B-13
154 (a) This chapter does not apply to any of the following
155 persons, activities, or services:
156 (1) Service in the case of emergency or domestic
157 upheaval, without compensation.
158 (2) Licensed medical professionals operating within the
159 scope of their normal practice.
160 (3) Personnel of the United States armed servicesArmed
161 Services performing their ordinary duties.
162 (4) Any public trade school or other public school or
163 school program under the purview of the State Board of
164 Education or a local board of education.
165 (5) Any person who only occasionally dresses hair and
166 receives no compensation therefor, or does any other act or
167 thing mentioned in this chapter, without holding himself or
168 herself out to the public as a provider of any practices
Page 6

herself out to the public as a provider of any practices
SB183 Enrolled
169 defined in this chapter for compensation.
170 (6) Departments in retail establishments where
171 cosmetics are demonstrated and offered for sale but where no
172 other acts of cosmetology or barbering are performed.
173 (7) The licensees of any county or municipal barber
174 board or commission in existence on August 1, 2013, unless
175 such board or commission elects, by resolution adopted by the
176 governing body of the county or municipality, to come under
177 the provisions of this chapter.
178 (8) Any person who practices as a Class 1 barber.
179 (b) Any person who practices natural hair styling as
180 defined in Section 34-7B-1, including facilities where only
181 natural hair styling is performed, shall not be required to
182 have a license issued by the board. Nothing in this section
183 shall be construed to limit the availability of a voluntary
184 natural hairstylist license to those who meet the requirements
185 of this chapter. Nothing in this section shall be construed to
186 limit the availability of a voluntary natural hairstylist
187 license to students enrolled in a public high school career
188 and technical education cosmetology program."
189 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
190 1, 2026.
